{"word":"προὐννέπω","slug":"προὐννέπω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προὐννέπω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><i>to proclaim, announce</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>πρ. τινὶ ὅτι . .</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <el>πρ. τινὰ χαίρειν</el> <i>I publicly bid</i> him hail, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}